ered on the brink of bankruptcy after a management shakeup and a productcycle refresh however oracle’s new products took the industry by storm and by  the company was the leader in the databasemanagement realmsuccess continued and as ellison was oracle’s largest shareholder he became one of the wealthiest people in the world ellison set his sights on growth through acquisitions and over the next several years he gobbled up several companies including peoplesoft siebel systems and sun microsystems all of which helped oracle reach a market cap of roughly  billion with some  employees by  americas cupwhen he’s not busy bolstering his software empire ellison races yachts his yacht rising sun is over  feet long—one of the largest privately owned vessels in the world and in  he joined the bmw oracle racing team and won the prestigious america’s cup the victory brought the cup to the united states for the first time in  years a win the team repeated in fact checkwe strive for accuracy and fairness if you see something that doesnt look right contact uscitation informationarticle titlelarry ellison biographycomauthorbiographycom editorswebsite namethe biographycom websiteurlhttpswwwbiographycompeoplelarryellisonaccess datepublisherae television networkslast updatedfebruary  original published datenasharesbio newslettersign up to receive updates from bio and ae networks larry ellison  wikipedia larry ellison from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from lawrence ellison this is the latest accepted revision reviewed on  july  jump to navigation search larry ellison larry ellison in october  born lawrence joseph ellison  august   age  manhattan new york us residence woodside california us nationality american alma mater university of illinois at urbanachampaign university of chicago occupation executive chairman and cto of oracle corporation years active –present known for cofounder and former ceo of oracle corporation salary us million  net worth us billion march  spouses adda quinn m  div  nancy wheeler jenkins m  div  barbara boothe m  div  melanie craft m  div  children david ellison megan ellison website larry ellison lawrence joseph ellison born august   is an american businessman entrepreneur and philanthropist who is cofounder of oracle corporation and was ceo from its founding until september  he is the executive chairman and chief technology officer of oracle as of february  he was listed by forbes magazine as the fifthwealthiest person in america and as the seventhwealthiest in the world with a fortune of  billion ellison was born in new york city and grew up in chicago he studied at the university of illinois at urbana–champaign and the university of chicago without graduating before moving to california in  while working at ampex in the early s he became influenced by edgar f codds research on relational database design which led in  to the formation of what became oracle oracle became a successful database vendor to mid and lowrange systems competing with sybase and microsoft sql server which led to ellison being listed by forbes as one of the richest men in the world ellison has donated up to  of his wealth to charity and has signed the giving pledge in addition to his work at oracle ellison has had success in yachting through oracle team usa he is a licensed aircraft pilot who owns two military jets contents  early life and education  early career and oracle  –  –  –present  personal life  yachting  aviation  tennis  homes  philanthropy  politics  see also  references  further reading  external links early life and educationedit larry ellison was born in new york city to an unwed jewish mother his biological father was an italian american united states army air corps pilot after ellison contracted pneumonia at the age of nine months his mother gave him to her aunt and uncle for adoption he did not meet his biological mother again until he was  ellison moved to chicagos south shore then a middleclass neighborhood he remembers his adoptive mother as warm and loving in contrast to his austere unsupportive and often distant adoptive father who adopted the name ellison to honor his point of entry into the united states ellis island louis ellison was a government employee who had made a small fortune in chicago real estate only to lose it during the great depression although ellison was raised in a reform jewish home by his adoptive parents who attended synagogue regularly he remained a religious skeptic ellison states while i think i am religious in one sense the particular dogmas of judaism are not dogmas i subscribe to i dont believe that they are real theyre interesting stories theyre interesting mythology and i certainly respect people who believe these are literally true but i dont i see no evidence for this stuff at age thirteen ellison refused to have a bar mitzvah celebration ellison says that his love affair with israel is not connected to religious sentiments but rather due to the innovative spirit of israelis in the technology sector ellison left the university of illinois at urbana–champaign after his second year not taking his final exams because his adoptive mother had just died after spending a summer in northern california he attended the university of chicago for one term where he first encountered computer design in  aged  he moved to northern california early career and oracleedit larry ellison lecturing at the oracle openworld san francisco  –edit during the s after a brief stint at amdahl corporation ellison began working for ampex corporation his projects included a database for the cia which he named oracle ellison was inspired by a paper written by edgar f codd on relational database systems called a relational model of data for large shared data banks in  he founded software development laboratories sdl with two partners and an investment of   of the money was his in  the company renamed itself relational software inc and in  officially became oracle systems corporation after its flagship product the oracle database ellison had heard about the ibm system r database also based on codds theories and wanted oracle to achieve compatibility with it but ibm made this impossible by refusing to share system rs code the initial release of oracle in  was called oracle  there was no oracle citation needed in  oracle laid off  of its workforce about  people because it was losing money this crisis which almost resulted in the companys bankruptcy came about because of oracles upfront marketing strategy in which sales people urged potential customers to buy the largest possible amount of software all at once the sales people then booked the value of future license sales in the current quarter thereby increasing their bonuses this became a problem when the future sales subsequently failed to materialize oracle eventually had to restate its earnings twice and had to settle classaction lawsuits arising from its having overstated its earnings ellison would later say that oracle had made an incredible business mistake although ibm dominated the mainframe relational database market with its db and sqlds database products it delayed entering the market for a relational database on unix and windows operating systems this left the door open for sybase oracle informix and eventually microsoft to dominate midrange systems and microcomputers around this time oracle fell behind sybase from  to  sybase was the fastestgrowing database company and the database industrys darling vendor but soon fell victim to merger mania sybases  merger with powersoft resulted in a loss of focus on its core database technology in  sybase sold the rights to its database software running under the windows operating system to microsoft corporation which now markets it under the name sql server in his early years at oracle larry ellison was named an award recipient in the high technology category for the ey entrepreneur of the year program –edit in  informix overtook sybase and became oracles most important rival the intense war between informix ceo phil white and ellison was front page silicon valley news for three years in april  informix announced a major revenue shortfall and earnings restatements phil white eventually landed in jail and ibm absorbed informix in  also in  ellison was made a director of apple computer after steve jobs returned to the company ellison resigned in  saying my schedule does not currently allow me to attend enough of the formal board meetings to warrant a role as a director with the defeat of informix and of sybase oracle enjoyed years of industry dominance until the rise of microsoft sql server in the late s and ibms acquisition of informix software in  to complement their db database as of update oracles main competition for new database licenses on unix linux and windows operating systems comes from ibms db and from microsoft sql server which only runs on windows ibms db still dominates the mainframe database market in  oracle corporation paid ellison a  salary a  bonus and other compensation of  in  ellison earned a total compensation of  which included a base salary of  a cash bonus of  and options granted of  in  he earned a total compensation of  which included a base salary of  a cash bonus of  no stock grants and options granted of  in the year ending may   he made  million in  forbes ranked him as the richest californian in april  after a tugofwar with ibm and hewlettpackard oracle announced its intent to buy sun microsystems on july   for the fourth year in a row oracles board awarded ellison another  million stock options on august   it was reported that ellison would be paid only  for his base salary for the fiscal year of  down from the  he was paid in fiscal  –presentedit the european union approved oracles acquisition of sun microsystems on january   and agreed that oracles acquisition of sun has the potential to revitalize important assets and create new and innovative products the sun acquisition also gave oracle control of the popular mysql open source database which sun had acquired in  on august   ellison denounced hewlettpackards board for firing ceo mark hurd writing that the hp board just made the worst personnel decision since the idiots on the apple board fired steve jobs many years ago ellison and hurd are close personal friends then on september  oracle hired hurd and made him copresident alongside safra a catz ellison retained the ceo position in march  the forbes list of billionaires ranked ellison as the sixthrichest person in the world and he is the thirdrichest american with an estimated net worth of us  billion on july   the wall street journal reported that ellison was the bestpaid executive in the last decade collecting a total compensation of us  billion in september  ellison was listed on the forbes list of billionaires as the fifth richest man in the world and was still the third richest american with a net worth of about  billion in september  ellison was again listed on the forbes list of billionaires as the third richest american citizen behind bill gates and warren buffett with a net worth of  billion in october  he was listed just behind david hamilton koch as the eighth richest person in the world according to the bloomberg billionaires index ellison owns stakes in salesforcecom netsuite quark biotechnology inc and astex pharmaceuticals in june  ellison agreed to buy  percent of the hawaiian island of lanai from david murdocks company castle  cooke the price was reported to be between  million and  million in  ellison agreed to settle a fouryearold insidertrading lawsuit by offering to pay  million to charity in oracles name in  according to the wall street journal ellison earned  million on september   ellison announced he would be stepping down with mark hurd and safra catz to become coceos he plans to become executive chairman and cto in november  oracle bought netsuite for  billion ellison owned  of netsuite at the time of the purchase making him  billion personally  personal lifeedit ellison has been married and divorced four times adda quinn from  to  nancy wheeler jenkins from  to  they married six months before ellison founded software development laboratories in  the couple divorced wheeler gave up any claim on her husbands company for  barbara boothe from  to  boothe was a former receptionist at relational software inc rsi they had two children david and megan who are film producers at skydance productions and annapurna pictures respectively melanie craft a romance novelist from  to  they married on december   at his woodside estate ellisons late friend steve jobs former ceo and cofounder of apple inc was the official wedding photographer and representative tom lantos officiated they divorced in  ellison made a brief cameo appearance in the  movie iron man  in  ellison purchased a  share of the bnp paribas open tennis tournament ellison owns many exotic cars including an audi r and a mclaren f his favorite is the acura nsx which he was known to give as gifts each year during its production ellison is also reportedly the owner of a lexus lfa and a lexus lshl yachtingedit bmw oracle racing was the challenger of record on behalf of the golden gate yacht club of san francisco for the  americas cup in valencia spain until eliminated from the  louis vuitton cup challengerselection series in the semifinals on february   ellisons yacht usa  won the second race in the best of three deed of gift series of the rd americas cup after winning the first race two days earlier securing a historic victory ellison and his bmw oracle team became the first challengers to win a deed of gift match the cup returned to american shores for the first time since  ellison served as a crew member in the second race previously ellison had filed several legal challenges through the golden gate yacht club against the way that ernesto bertarelli also one of the worlds richest men proposed to organize the rd americas cup following the  victory of bertarellis team alinghi the races were finally heldclarification needed in february  in valencia spain in  ellisons oracles team introduced kite yachting into the american cup environment the kite traction flying lasted about  minutes in new zealand in  ellison ended his ownership of the eighth largest yacht in the world named rising sun he sold his remaining shares in the yacht to music and film mogul david geffen rising sun is  feet  metres long and reportedly cost over  million to build he downsized to musashi a foot metre yacht built by feadship on september   ellisons oracle team usa defeated emirates team new zealand to win the th americas cup in san francisco bay california oracle team usa had been penalized two points in the final for cheating by some team members during the americas cup world series warmup events aviationedit ellison is a licensed pilot who has owned several aircraft he was cited by the city of san jose california for violating its limits on latenight takeoffs and landings from san jose mineta international airport by planes weighing more than  pounds  kg in january  ellison sued over the interpretation of the airport rule contending that his gulfstream v plane is certified by the manufacturer to fly at two weights  pounds and at  pounds for heavier loads or long flights requiring more fuel but the pilot only lands the plane in san jose when it weighs  pounds or less and has the logs to prove it us district judge jeremy fogel ruled in ellisons favor in june  calling for a waiver for ellisons jet but did not invalidate the curfew ellison also owns at least two military jets a siaimarchetti s a training aircraft designed in italy and a decommissioned mig which the us government has refused him permission to import tennisedit in  larry purchased the indian wells tennis garden tennis facility in californias coachella valley and the indian wells masters tournament both of which he still owns homesedit ellison styled his estimated  million woodside california estate after feudal japanese architecture complete with a manmade acre  m lake and an extensive seismic retrofit in  and  he purchased more than  properties in malibu california worth more than  million the  million ellison spent on five contiguous lots at malibus carbon beach made this the most costly residential transaction in united states history until ron perelman sold his palm beach florida compound for  million later that same year his entertainment system cost  million and includes a rock concertsized video projector at one end of a drained swimming pool using the gaping hole as a giant subwoofer in early  ellison purchased the astors beechwood mansion  formerly the summer home of the astor family  in newport rhode island for  million in  he purchased the acre porcupine creek estate and private golf course in rancho mirage california for  million the property was formerly the home of yellowstone club founders edra and tim blixseth and was sold to ellison by creditors following their divorce and bankruptcy on june   the governor of hawaii neil abercrombie declared that ellison had signed an agreement to buy most of the island of lanai from the castle  cooke company owned by david h murdock following the purchase ellison owns  of lanai hawaiis sixthlargest island philanthropyedit in  ellison shattered his elbow in a highspeed bicycle crash his search for a highly skilled orthopedic surgeon led him to dr michael w chapman at the university of california davis impressed by his care ellison donated  million to seed the lawrence j ellison musculoskeletal research center in  the lawrence j ellison ambulatory care center opened on the sacramento campus of the uc davis medical center in order to settle an insider trading lawsuit arising from ellisons selling nearly  billion of oracle stock he was allowed to donate  million to his own charitable foundation without admitting wrongdoing a california judge refused to allow oracle to pay ellisons legal fees of  million ellisons lawyer had argued that if ellison were to pay the fees that could be construed as an admission of guilt his charitable donations to stanford university raised questions about the independence of two stanford professors who evaluated the cases merits for oracle in response to the september  terrorist attacks ellison made a controversial offer to donate software to the federal government that would enable it to build and run a national identification database and issue id cards forbess  list of charitable donations made by the wealthiest  americans stated that ellison had donated  about  of his estimated personal wealth in june  he announced he would not honor his earlier pledge of  million to harvard university claiming it was due to the departure of former president lawrence summers oracle spokesman bob wynne announced it was really larry summers brainchild and once it looked like larry summers was leaving larry ellison reconsidered  it was larry ellison and larry summers that had initially come up with this notion in  ellison pledged  to fortify a community centre in sderot israel after discovering that the building was not fortified against rocket attacks other charitable donations by ellison include a  million donation to the friends of the israel defense forces about which he said in my mind there is no greater honor than supporting some of the bravest people in the world  these men and women come together with indefatigable purpose to defend israel and strive to coexist in peace in august  it was reported that ellison is one of the  billionaires who have signed the giving pledge ellison wrote many years ago i put virtually all of my assets into a trust with the intent of giving away at least  percent of my wealth to charitable causes i have already given hundreds of millions of dollars to medical research and education and i will give billions more over time until now i have done this giving quietly because i have long believed that charitable giving is a personal and private matter in may  ellison donated  million to university of southern california for establishing a cancer research center lawrence j ellison institute for transformative medicine of usc politicsedit ellison was critical of nsa whistleblower edward snowden saying that snowden had yet to identify a single person who had been wrongly injured by the nsa’s data collection he has donated to both democratic and republican politicians and in late  hosted republican senator rand paul at a fundraiser at his home ellison is one of the top donors to conservative solutions pac a super pac supporting marco rubios  presidential bid as of february  ellison had given  million overall to the pac see alsoedit biography portal business and economics portal information technology portal san francisco bay area portal ellison medical foundation referencesedit  lawrence j ellison  executive biography oracle retrieved july     compensation information for lawrence j ellison chairman and chief technology officer of oracle corp  salarycom salarycom   httpswwwforbescomprofilelarryellison  a b c larry ellison forbes retrieved november     rohrlich justin august   ceos gone wild larry ellison minyanvillecom retrieved june     the jewish billionaires of forbes jspace march   archived from the original on march   retrieved march     the worlds  richest jews – the jerusalem post september     serwer andy boorstin julia sung jessica the next richest man in the world larry ellison is a very lucky guy he has more money than anyone—except bill gates fortune cnn money   symonds matthew ellison larry  softwar an intimate portrait of larry ellison and oracle new york simon  schuster pp – isbn    a b symonds matthew ellison larry  softwar an intimate portrait of larry ellison and oracle new york simon and schuster pp – isbn    rohrlich justin rags to riches ceos larry ellison minyanvillecom retrieved march     symonds and e