 would make an impression in his new life youtube screenshot ellison bounced around from job to job including stints at companies like wells fargo and the mainframe manufacturer amdahl along the way he learned his computer and programming skills wikimedia commons the turning point came when ellison came to work for the electronics company ampex which had a contract to build a database for the cia codenamed oracle youtube screenshot in  ellison and partners bob miner and ed oates founded a new company software development laboratories the company started with  of funding  of which came out of ellisons own pocket cofounders of oracleoracle ellison and company were inspired by ibm computer scientist edgar f codds theories for a socalled relational database — a way for computer systems to store and access information nowadays theyre taken for granted but in the s they were a revolutionary idea flickrpeter hardy the first version of the oracle database was version  — there was no version  in  the company renamed itself relational software inc and in  it formally became oracle systems corp after its flagship product ap photoeric risberg as one of the key drivers of the growing computer industry oracle grew fast in  oracle had its initial public offering reporting revenue of  million ap images still in  oracle had to lay off  of its workforce about  people because of what ellison later described as an incredible business mistake oracle allowed its salespeople to book future sales in the current quarter meaning all its numbers were skewed it resulted in lawsuits and trouble with regulators reutersrobert galbraith it didnt get the decade off to a great start after adjusting for that huge error oracle was said to be close to bankruptcy at the same time rivals like sybase were eating away at oracles market share michael bradleygetty images it took a few years but by  ellison and oracle managed to right the course with some new blood and the popular oracle database flickr d miller ellison is known for his willingness to trashtalk competitors for much of the s he and oracle were locked in a publicrelations battle with the competitor informix which went so far as to place a dinosaur crossing billboard outside oracles silicon valley offices at one point reddit but oracle just kept steamrolling over the competition and with ellison as oracles major shareholder his millions kept rolling in he started to indulge some expensive hobbies — including yacht racing thats ellison at the helm during a  race ian mainsbridgeap images ellison even managed to turn a potential loss into a big win in  ellisons protégé marc benioff left oracle to work on a new startup called salesforcecom ellison was an early investor putting  million into his friends new venture mike nudelmanbusiness insider when benioff found out that ellison had oracle working on a direct competitor to salesforces product he tried to force his mentor to quit the companys board instead ellison forced benioff to fire him — meaning ellison kept his shares in salesforce robert galbraithreuters given that salesforce is now a  billion company ellison personally profits even when his competitors do well it has led to a rocky relationship between the two executives that continues to this day with the two taking shots at each other in the press stephen dunngetty images in fact salesforce aside the dotcom boom of the late s benefited oracle too all of those new dotcom companies needed databases and oracle was there to sell them laurent gillieronap images when steve jobs returned to apple as ceo in  he asked ellison to sit on the board ellison stuck around for a while but felt that he couldnt devote the time mousse moussereuters with the coffers overflowing ellison was able to lead oracle through a spending spree once the dotcom boom was over and prices were low in  for example oracle snapped up the hr software provider peoplesoft for  billion reutersap and in  oracle bought sun microsystems a server company that started at about the same time as oracle in  that acquisition gave oracle lots of key technology including control over the popular mysql database david paul morrisgetty images starting in the s ellison started to take more of a backseat handing more responsibilities to trusted lieutenants like mark hurd and safra catz  ap  but his spending didnt slow down in  he bought the entire hawaiian island of lanai for an estimated  million four seasons resorts lanai ellison has been married and divorced four times coupled with his extreme wealth its given him a reputation as an international jetsetting playboy hes said to be dating nikita kahn a model and actress photo by chris kleponispoolgetty images in  ellison officially stepped down as oracle ceo handing control over to hurd and katz at that time ellison held the title of fifthrichest person in the world getty in  ellison scored a personal coup back in  he made a  million investment in exoracle exec evan goldbergs startup businessmanagement software firm netsuite  youtubescreenshot  which ended up working out when netsuite ceo zach nelson ended up negotiating the sale of the company to oracle for  billion netting ellison a cool  billion in cash for this stake netsuite investor t rowe price tried to block the deal citing ellisons conflict of interest but it closed in november  the demo conference  flickr oracle is going through a painful transition it was slow to adopt the cloud technology that is so popular in oracles crucial enterprise market though its made more aggressive moves recently the upstart amazon web services for instance is stealing oracle customers away at an alarming pace business insider so while ellison is technically not in the top spot hes still oracles chairman and cto working to navigate the company through these choppy waters and the rest as they say is history ap photobernat armangue see also the rise of satya nadella the gamechanging ceo of microsoft more features larry ellison orac